What is Git?

Your answer was close.

Better Answer

Git is a distributed version control system used to track source code changes. It helps multiple developers work on the same project, maintain code history, and manage versions of the application.

Project-Based Answer

In my project, we use Git to manage source code, track changes, maintain version history, and collaborate with developers.

10. Difference Between Git and GitHub?
Answer
Git	GitHub
Version Control System	Repository Hosting Platform
Installed on local machine	Cloud-based service
Tracks code changes	Stores Git repositories
Used for commit, branch, merge	Used for collaboration and Pull Requests
Interview Answer

Git is a version control system used to track source code changes, whereas GitHub is a cloud platform used to host and manage Git repositories.

