12. What is a Pull Request (PR)?

Your answer:

When we merge to main branch then we create PR.

Small correction:

Correct Answer

A Pull Request is a request to merge code changes from one branch to another branch. Before merging, team members review the code, provide comments, and approve the changes.

Example
feature branch
      ↓
Pull Request
      ↓
Code Review
      ↓
Approval
      ↓
main branch
Project-Based Answer

In my project, developers create feature branches and make code changes. After testing, they raise a Pull Request to merge changes into the main branch. The code is reviewed and approved before merging.

Quick Interview Round

Q: What is the difference between git pull and git push?

A:

git pull downloads changes from remote to local, whereas git push uploads local changes to the remote repository.

Q: Why do we use Pull Requests?

A:

To perform code reviews, maintain code quality, and control code changes before merging into the main branch.
